  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Tunturi Hotel Suites can be booked on either bed and breakfast or half board. All meals are taken in the Tunturi Hotel's main building (approx. 150 metre walk).</p>
<p>An extensive hot and cold buffet is included. Each day you can fuel up for the day with a variety of continental breakfast items, with additional hot options.</p>
<p>You have the option to pre-book dinner, which is served in the Tunturi main building. You can enjoy a three course buffet dinner with a choice of main courses, including a vegetarian option, two desserts, soup and a salad buffet. </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Christmas and New Year meals are included.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>The Tunturi Hotel Suites are part of the lovely <a data-udi="umb://document/3f5398805f5841a28e1f5829945f8748" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3f5398805f5841a28e1f5829945f8748}" title="Tunturi Hotel">Tunturi Hotel</a> complex, offering cosy accommodation, welcoming public spaces with wood panelling, and tasty meals served in the main restaurant. The hotel enjoys a peaceful setting 200 metres from the village centre, next to the start of the cross-country ski tracks. The Suites are in four separate buildings up to 200 metres (2 minute walk) from the hotels main reception building and restaurants. </span></p>
<h2>Central accommodation</h2>
<p>The Tunturi Hotel Suites enjoy a serene setting set back from the village centre, surrounded by lovely snow-covered trees with easy access to cross-country ski routes. The main village is just a short walk away, where you'll find a variety of gift stores, restaurants and cafes, as well as toboggan slopes and the bus stop that will take you to the ski resort.</p>
<h2>Comfortable accommodation</h2>
<p>All of the suites we offer provide cosy and comfortable accommodation with a great location in <a data-udi="umb://document/b8a6a8fa31c94e959dc5959c1881f2d5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b8a6a8fa31c94e959dc5959c1881f2d5}" title="Saariselka"><span>Saariselkä</span></a>. The suites are equipped with everything you may need for a week in <a data-udi="umb://document/2da7ac9814d44a75af6718b02ca02250" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2da7ac9814d44a75af6718b02ca02250}" title="Lapland/Finland">Finnish Lapland</a>, including a small kitchenette, cosy bedrooms and access to the Tunturi Hotel facilities.  </p>
<h2>Bar and restaurants</h2>
<p>The main Tunturi building houses the lobby and restaurant, where you will eat breakfast and dinner. If you have opted into the half board option, you can enjoy a three course buffet style meal, where you will have a variety of different dishes to choose from including Lappish specialities.</p>
<p>After a day of exploring <span>Saariselkä</span>, you can warm up in the cosy and welcoming communal areas with wood panelling, or enjoy a drink or snack in the Bar and Grill Pirtti - it has a home away from home feel serving a range of Lappish pub food, pizzas and burgers (pay locally). </p>]]></description>
